CARRYING FLUIDS FOR LIQUID Fungal Spores Formulations

Abstract
translated from Portuguese

fluidos carreadores para formulaes de esporo fngico lquido. a presente inveno refere-se a uma preparao lquida compreendendo pelo menos um ster carboxlico como definido e esporos fngicos e um mtodo para controle de fungos fitopatognicos, insetos e/ou nematdeos em ou sobre uma planta, para realar o crescimento de uma planta ou para aumentar o rendimento da planta ou a sade da raiz compreendendo aplicar uma quantidade eficaz da preparao lquida ou da composio lquida de acordo com a inveno a uma referida planta ou a um locus onde plantas esto crescendo ou pretende-se cultiv-las.Carrier fluids for liquid fungal spore formulations. The present invention relates to a liquid preparation comprising at least one carboxylic ester as defined and fungal spores and a method for controlling phytopathogenic fungi, insects and/or nematodes in or on a plant, for enhancing the growth of a plant or for increasing plant yield or root health comprising applying an effective amount of the liquid preparation or liquid composition according to the invention to said plant or to a locus where plants are growing or are intended to be cultivated.

translated from Portuguese

Relatrio Descritivo da Patente de Inveno para FLUIDOS CARREADORES PARA FORMULAES DE ESPORO FNGICO LQUIDO.Invention Patent Descriptive Report for "CARRYING FLUIDS FOR LIQUID Fungal Spores Formulations".

[0001] Os agentes de controle biolgico (BCAs) tornam-se cada vez mais importantes na rea de proteo de plantas, seja para combater vrias pragas de fungos ou insetos ou para melhorar a sade das plantas. Embora tambm estejam disponveis viroses que podem ser usadas como agentes de controle biolgico, principalmente BCAs baseados em bactrias e fungos so usados nesta rea. A forma mais proeminente de agentes de controle biolgico baseados em fungos so os esporos assexuados chamados condios, bem como blastsporos, mas tambm outros propgulos fngicos podem ser agentes promissores, tais como fragmentos de (micro)esclercio, ascsporos, basidisporos, clamidsporos ou de hifas.[0001] Biological control agents (BCAs) are becoming increasingly important in the area of plant protection, whether to combat various fungal or insect pests or to improve plant health. Although viruses are also available that can be used as biological control agents, mainly BCAs based on bacteria and fungi are used in this area. The most prominent form of fungal-based biological control agents are asexual spores called conidia, as well as blastospores, but also other fungal propagules can be promising agents, such as fragments of (micro) sclerotia, ascospores, basidiospores, chlamydospores or hyphae .

[0002] Ao contrrio de muitos esporos baseados em bactrias, tal como esporos de bacilos, muitos esporos de fungos so menos robustos e provou ser difcil fornecer esporos de fungos em uma forma que atenda s necessidades de produtos comerciais, em particular estabilidade de armazenamento aceitvel em certas temperaturas.[0002] Unlike many bacterial-based spores, such as bacillus spores, many fungal spores are less robust and have proved difficult to provide fungal spores in a form that meets the needs of commercial products, in particular acceptable storage stability at certain temperatures.

[0003] O fornecimento de formulaes adequadas para agentes de controle biolgico, todavia, ainda representa um desafio devido aos muitos fatores que contribuem para a eficcia da formulao final, tal como a natureza do agente de controle biolgico, estabilidade trmica e vida de prateleira bem como efeitos da formulao na aplicao.[0003] The provision of suitable formulations for biological control agents, however, still poses a challenge due to the many factors that contribute to the effectiveness of the final formulation, such as the nature of the biological control agent, thermal stability and good shelf life. as effects of the formulation on the application.

[0004] As formulaes adequadas so misturas homogneas e estveis de ingredientes ativos e inertes que tornam o produto final mais simples, seguro e eficaz para aplicar a um alvo.[0004] Suitable formulations are homogeneous and stable mixtures of active and inert ingredients that make the final product simpler, safer and more effective to apply to a target.

[0005] As formulaes comumente usadas para agentes de controle biolgico incluem WP, uma formulao slida micronizada na forma de p e normalmente aplicada como partculas suspensas aps a disperso em gua, e WG, uma formulao que consiste em grnulos a serem aplicados aps desintegrao e disperso em gua. Os grnulos de um produto WG tm partculas distintas na faixa de 0,2 a 4 mm. Os grnulos dispersveis em gua podem ser formados por tcnicas de aglomerao, secagem por pulverizao ou extruso. As formulaes de WP so produzidas com bastante facilidade, mas so empoeiradas. Alm disso, elas no so fceis de dosar no campo. As formulaes WG so mais fceis de manusear para o usurio e, em geral, tm menor teor de poeira do que as formulaes WP.[0005] Formulations commonly used for biological control agents include WP, a micronized solid formulation in powder form and normally applied as suspended particles after dispersion in water, and WG, a formulation consisting of granules to be applied after disintegration and dispersion in water. The granules of a WG product have distinct particles in the range of 0.2 to 4 mm. Water-dispersible granules can be formed by agglomeration, spray drying or extrusion techniques. WP formulations are produced quite easily, but are dusty. In addition, they are not easy to dose in the field. WG formulations are easier to handle for the user and, in general, have less dust content than WP formulations.

[0006] Um exemplo para uma formulao lquida SC, uma suspenso base de gua de ingrediente ativo slido em um fluido normalmente destinado diluio com gua antes do uso. Outro tipo de formulao lquida EC, uma soluo de ingrediente ativo combinado com tensoativos como, por exemplo, agentes emulsificantes em um solvente orgnico insolvel em gua que formar uma emulso quando adicionado gua.[0006] An example for a liquid formulation is SC, a water-based suspension of solid active ingredient in a fluid normally intended for dilution with water before use. Another type of liquid formulation is EC, an active ingredient solution combined with surfactants, for example, emulsifying agents in a water-insoluble organic solvent that will form an emulsion when added to water.

[0007] Um enorme nmero de formulantes tem sido utilizado em formulaes experimentais e comerciais de agentes de controle biolgico (para uma descrio e lista mais detalhadas, veja Schisler et al., Phytopathology, Vol 94, No. 11, 2004). Geralmente, os formulantes podem ser agrupados como carreadores (enchimentos, extensores) ou formulantes que melhoram as propriedades qumicas, fsicas, fisiolgicas ou nutricionais da biomassa formulada.[0007] A huge number of formulants have been used in experimental and commercial formulations of biological control agents (for a more detailed description and list, see Schisler et al., Phytopathology, Vol 94, No. 11, 2004). Generally, formulants can be grouped as carriers (fillers, extenders) or formulants that improve the chemical, physical, physiological or nutritional properties of the formulated biomass.

[0008] Estabilidade, particularmente estabilidade de armazenamento de BCAs com base em ativos fngicos durante um longo perodo de tempo em temperaturas iguais ou superiores temperatura ambiente um desafio particular devido natureza delicada dos condios fngicos. Como muitos organismos vivos, os condios fngicos em seu estado dormente so sensveis s influncias ambientais como, por exemplo, gua, ar (oxignio),[0008] Stability, particularly storage stability of BCAs based on fungal assets over a long period of time at or above room temperature is a particular challenge due to the delicate nature of fungal conidia. Like many living organisms, fungal conidia in their dormant state are sensitive to environmental influences, such as water, air (oxygen),

temperatura, irradiao e etc. Alguns fatores podem desencadear a germinao, enquanto outros podem ter efeitos prejudiciais para a viabilidade do esporo. Para excluir a gua, leos como leos minerais brancos (parafnicos) ou leos vegetais so normalmente usados para preparar formulaes lquidas de esporos de fungos. Muitos desses leos fornecem alguma vida de prateleira para organismos fngicos. Os leos vegetais so de origem natural e so essencialmente triglicerdeos de cido carboxlico mistos compostos por glicerina e cidos graxos C12-C18 saturados e insaturados; eles tambm contm quantidades variveis de ceras naturais. As composies dos leos vegetais so variveis e dependem de uma srie de fatores como variedades de plantas, fatores ambientais (por exemplo, solo, nutrientes) e clima, para citar apenas alguns. Assim, uma qualidade e composio constantes so difceis de alcanar ao longo de vrios anos e/ou geografias. Outro fator limitante no uso industrial de leos vegetais que todos esses leos so suscetveis a se tornarem ranosos, isto , quando exposto ao ar, luz, umidade ou por ao bacteriana, isso resulta em odor desagradvel, formao descontrolada de resduos polimricos e a liberao de cidos graxos livres que promovem ainda mais a decomposio de uma forma autocataltica. Portanto, medidas preventivas, tal como excluso de luz, oxignio, temperaturas elevadas e contaminao microbiana indesejada so necessrias e contramedidas como o uso de antioxidantes, eliminadores de radicais ou biocidas devem ser aplicadas para garantir a estabilidade das composies base de leo vegetal.temperature, irradiation and etc. Some factors can trigger germination, while others can have detrimental effects on spore viability. To exclude water, oils such as white mineral oils (paraffinic) or vegetable oils are commonly used to prepare liquid fungal spore formulations. Many of these oils provide some shelf life for fungal organisms. Vegetable oils are of natural origin and are essentially mixed carboxylic acid triglycerides composed of glycerin and saturated and unsaturated C12-C18 fatty acids; they also contain varying amounts of natural waxes. The compositions of vegetable oils are variable and depend on a number of factors such as plant varieties, environmental factors (for example, soil, nutrients) and climate, to name just a few. Thus, constant quality and composition are difficult to achieve over several years and / or geographies. Another limiting factor in the industrial use of vegetable oils is that all of these oils are susceptible to becoming rancid, that is, when exposed to air, light, moisture or by bacterial action, this results in an unpleasant odor, uncontrolled formation of polymeric residues and the release of free fatty acids that further promote the decomposition of an autocatalytic form. Therefore, preventive measures, such as exclusion of light, oxygen, high temperatures and unwanted microbial contamination are necessary and countermeasures such as the use of antioxidants, radical scavengers or biocides must be applied to guarantee the stability of vegetable oil-based compositions.

[0009] Um exemplo para uma formulao de um agente de controle biolgico descrito em Torres et al., 2003, J Appl Microbiol, 94(2), pp: 330-9). No entanto, claro que uma formulao que preserva a viabilidade do agente de controle biolgico, por exemplo,[0009] An example for a formulation of a biological control agent is described in Torres et al., 2003, J Appl Microbiol, 94 (2), pp: 330-9). However, it is clear that a formulation that preserves the viability of the biological control agent, for example,

esporos de fungos, de mais de 70% por 4 meses a 4 graus C, no adequada para o uso dirio no campo. Em vez disso, desejvel que as formulaes de agentes de controle biolgico tenham uma vida de prateleira suficiente, mesmo em condies onde o armazenamento a frio no possvel.fungal spores, of more than 70% for 4 months at 4 degrees C, are not suitable for daily use in the field. Instead, it is desirable that formulations of biological control agents have sufficient shelf life, even in conditions where cold storage is not possible.

[0010] Kim et al., 2010 (J.S. Kim, Y.H. Je, J. Y. Roh, Journal of Industrial Microbiology & Biotechnology 2010, vol 37 (edio 4), pp, 419ff) divulgam que condios do fungo Isaria fumosorosea apresentam estabilidade melhorada durante um tratamento trmico de 2 e 8 horas a 50 C quando dispersos em leos (soja, milho, caroo de algodo, leo de parafina, oleato de metila) em comparao com a disperso em gua.[0010] Kim et al., 2010 (JS Kim, YH Je, JY Roh, Journal of Industrial Microbiology & Biotechnology 2010, vol 37 (edition 4), pp, 419ff) disclose that conidia of the fungus Isaria fumosorosea show improved stability during a heat treatment of 2 and 8 hours at 50 C when dispersed in oils (soy, corn, cottonseed, paraffin oil, methyl oleate) compared to dispersion in water.

[0011] Mbarga et al., 2014 (Biological Control 2014, vol. 77, pp.15ff) descobriram que Trichoderma asperellum frmulado em leo de soja com diferentes emulsionantes apresenta vida de prateleira melhorada em comparao a uma disperso de condios em gua.[0011] Mbarga et al., 2014 (Biological Control 2014, vol. 77, pp.15ff) found that Trichoderma asperellum formulated in soy oil with different emulsifiers has improved shelf life compared to a dispersion of conidia in water.

[0012] Outros lquidos como, por exemplo, trisiloxanos etoxilados (por exemplo, Break-Thru S240) so alternativas adequadas e fornecem preparaes estveis, por exemplo, com P. Lilacinum (BioAct, veja WO2016/050726), entretanto, fabricao de tais trisiloxanos e, portanto, dos prprios produtos so caros.[0012] Other liquids such as ethoxylated trisiloxanes (eg Break-Thru S240) are suitable alternatives and provide stable preparations, for example, with P. Lilacinum (BioAct, see WO2016 / 050726), however, such trisiloxanes and, therefore, the products themselves are expensive.

[0013] EP 1 886 570 A2 descreve uma formulao agroquimicamente ativa de esporos microbianos compreendendo um certo ster e um tensoativo. Os valores absolutos para estabilidade sugerem boas viabilidades, entretanto, a estabilidade geral no particularmente alta, como pode ser mostrado pela comparao de viabilidades relativas: as viabilidades dos esporos aps armazenamento por 8 semanas a 40 C caem para nveis to baixos quanto 5,86% (Tabela 1, formulao 4). WO 2009/126473 A1 descreve uma formulao base de gua contendo bactrias e certos aditivos no aquosos miscveis em gua e/ou imiscveis em gua. WO 2016/189329 A1 descreve o uso de cidos graxos e derivados de cidos graxos em combinao com certas espcies de fungos. Begonya Vicedo et al. (Archives of Microbiology, vol. 184, no. 5, p. 316ff) descreve um dicido carboxlico parcialmente esterificado (isto , monoetilster de cido adpico, ou AAME) para controlar doenas causadas por Boytritis sp.[0013] EP 1 886 570 A2 describes an agrochemically active formulation of microbial spores comprising a certain ester and a surfactant. The absolute values for stability suggest good viability, however, the overall stability is not particularly high, as can be shown by comparing relative viability: spore viability after storage for 8 weeks at 40 C drops to levels as low as 5, 86% (Table 1, formulation 4). WO 2009/126473 A1 describes a water-based formulation containing bacteria and certain water-miscible and / or water-immiscible non-aqueous additives. [0079] BCAs so organismos vivos em uma forma dormente.[0079] BCAs are living organisms in a dormant form.

Consequentemente, as formulaes compreendendo uma baixa concentrao de gua ou mesmo sendo essencialmente isentas de gua so um tipo de formulao preferencial para BCAs. Por outro lado, certos BCAs tambm podem ser formulados em um maior teor de gua. Se a gua estiver presente, tal gua vir principalmente de gua livre residual no p de esporo seco ou traos de gua em outros formulantes. Consequentemente, concentraes de gua entre 0 e 8% so possveis devido a esses fatos, cuja faixa ento cairia na definio de essencialmente livre de gua. Preferivelmente, a concentrao de gua varia entre 0 e 6%, mais preferivelmente entre 0 e 4% como entre 2 e 4%. Consequentemente, as concentraes de gua exemplares incluem 2%, 3%, 4%, 5% e 6%.Consequently, formulations comprising a low water concentration or even being essentially water-free are a type of formulation preferred for BCAs. On the other hand, certain BCAs can also be formulated in a higher water content. If water is present, such water will come mainly from residual free water in the dry spore powder or traces of water in other formulants. Consequently, concentrations of water between 0 and 8% are possible due to these facts, whose range would then fall under the definition of essentially free of water. Preferably, the water concentration varies between 0 and 6%, more preferably between 0 and 4% and between 2 and 4%. Consequently, exemplary water concentrations include 2%, 3%, 4%, 5% and 6%.

Exemplos adicionais e particularmente enfatizados de tais propriedades so aumento da resistncia das plantas contra pragas animais e microbianas, tais como contra insetos, aracndeos, nematdeos, caros, lesmas e caracis devido, por exemplo, s toxinas formadas nas plantas, em particular aquelas formadas nas plantas pelo material gentico de Bacillus thuringiensis (por exemplo, pelos genes CryIA(a), CryIA(b), CryIA(c), CryIIA, CryIIIA, CryIIIB2, Cry9c Cry2Ab, Cry3Bb e CryIF e tambm combinaes dos mesmos), alm disso, aumentaram a resistncia das plantas contra fungos fitopatognicos, bactrias e/ou vrus devido, por exemplo, resistncia sistmica adquirida (SAR), sisteminas, fitoalexinas, eliciadores e tambm genes de resistncia e protenas e toxinas correspondentemente expressas, e tambm aumentaram a tolerncia das plantas a certos compostos herbicidamente ativos, por exemplo, imidazolinonas, sulfonilureias, glifosatos ou fosfinotricina (por exemplo, o gene "PAT"). Os genes que conferem as caractersticas desejadas em questo tambm podem estar presentes em combinaes com um outro mas plantas transgnicas. Exemplos de plantas transgnicas que podem ser mencionadas so as plantas de cultivo importantes, tais como os cereais (trigo, arroz, triticale, cevada, centeio, aveia), milho, soja, batata, beterraba sacarina, cana-de-acar, tomate, ervilha e outros tipos de vegetais, algodo, tabaco, colza e tambm fruteiras (com as frutas mas, pras, frutas ctricas e uvas), com particular nfase sendo dada ao milho, soja, trigo, arroz, batata, algodo, cana-de-acar, tabaco e colza. As caractersticas que so particularmente enfatizadas so o aumento da resistncia das plantas a insetos, aracndeos, nematdeos e lesmas e caracis.[00134] Transgenic plants or plant cultivars (those obtained by genetic engineering) that should be treated with preference according to the invention include all plants that, through genetic modification, received genetic material that confer particular advantageous useful properties ("characteristics ") to these plants. Examples of such properties are better plant growth, greater tolerance to high or low temperatures, greater tolerance to drought or to water levels or soil salinity, better flowering performance, easier harvesting, accelerated ripening, higher yields, higher quality and / or greater nutritional value of the harvested products, better storage time and / or processability of the harvested products. Additional and particularly emphasized examples of such properties are increased resistance of plants against animal and microbial pests, such as against insects, arachnids, nematodes, mites, slugs and snails due, for example, to toxins formed in plants, in particular those formed in plants. plants by the genetic material of Bacillus thuringiensis (for example, by the CryIA (a), CryIA (b), CryIA (c), CryIIA, CryIIIA, CryIIIB2, Cry9c Cry2Ab, Cry3Bb and CryIF genes and combinations thereof, in addition, increased the resistance of plants against phytopathogenic fungi, bacteria and / or viruses due, for example, to the acquired systemic resistance (SAR), systems, phytoalexins, elicitors and also resistance genes and correspondingly expressed proteins and toxins, and also increased the tolerance of plants to certain herbicidally active compounds, for example, imidazolinones, sulfonylureas, glyphosates or phosphinothricin (for example, the "PAT" gene). The genes that confer the desired characteristics in question may also be present in combinations with one another but transgenic plants. Examples of transgenic plants that can be mentioned are important crop plants, such as cereals (wheat, rice, triticale, barley, rye, oats), corn, soybeans, potatoes, sugar beet, sugar cane, tomatoes, peas and other types of vegetables, cotton, tobacco, rapeseed and also fruit trees (with apples, pears, citrus fruits and grapes), with particular emphasis being placed on corn, soybeans, wheat, rice, potatoes, cotton, cane -sugar, tobacco and rapeseed. The characteristics that are particularly emphasized are the increased resistance of plants to insects, arachnids, nematodes and slugs and snails.

[00137] 3 g de p de esporo puro de Purpureocillium lilacinum foram transferidos para um recipiente de formulao (recipiente de mistura IKA Tipo DT-20 com ferramenta de disperso para Ultra Turrax) usando uma colher estril. 12 mL de fluido foram adicionados ao respectivo recipiente de formulao e dispersos usando controle de unidade de tubo ultra turrax durante 1 minuto a 3000 rpm; mudana de direo aps 30 segundos. Aps isso 2,8 mL foram transferidos em quatro garrafas de amostra (Frasconete Wheaton Serum, Tipo I) deixando espao areo e firmemente fechada usando tampas crimpada (Macherey Nagel tipo N 13). Posteriormente todas as garrafas de amostra foram transferidas para um conjunto de incubadora a 30 C e armazenados durante um determinado tempo.[00137] 3 g of pure Purpureocillium lilacinum spore powder was transferred to a formulation vessel (IKA Type DT-20 mixing vessel with Ultra Turrax dispersion tool) using a sterile spoon. 12 mL of fluid was added to the respective formulation container and dispersed using ultra turrax tube unit control for 1 minute at 3000 rpm; change of direction after 30 seconds. After that, 2.8 mL were transferred in four sample bottles (Frasconete Wheaton Serum, Type I) leaving air space and firmly closed using crimped lids (Macherey - Nagel type N 13). Subsequently, all sample bottles were transferred to an incubator set at 30 C and stored for a certain time.

[00138] Em intervalos irregulares uma amostra foi recuperada do local de armazenamento e analisada para viabilidade do esporo. Para este propsito, as amostras originais foram completamente homogeneizadas. Alquotas de 0,25 g ou 250 L de cada amostra foram transferidas para tubos falcon de 50 mL. Os tubos foram preenchidos at 25 g usando uma soluo aquosa estril contendo 2% de Tween 80 e homogeinizados em vrtice para alcanar a primeira etapa de diluio (diluio de 1:100). Esta diluio foi usada para diluio adicional e manchamento em gar.[00138] At irregular intervals a sample was recovered from the storage site and analyzed for spore viability. For this purpose, the original samples were completely homogenized. 0.25 g or 250 L aliquots of each sample were transferred to 50 mL falcon tubes. The tubes were filled to 25 g using a sterile aqueous solution containing 2% Tween 80 and vortexed to achieve the first dilution step (1: 100 dilution). This dilution was used for further dilution and agar staining.

[00139] No todas as amostras bem misturadas ou totalmente misturadas em 2% de Tween 80. Para estas amostras, um mtodo alternativo de disperso/diluio foi aplicado onde a fase oleosa foi retirada dos esporos primeiro: 0,25 g ou 250 L de amostra so pesados em um tubo Eppendorf de 2 mL, e 0,5 mL de 2% de Tween 80 adicionado, e a mistura transferida para uma centrfuga Eppendorf onde ela centrifugada durante 1 minuto a 10,000 rpm. O sobrenadante (= fase oleosa superior) descartado usando uma pipeta. Posteriormente 250 L de Breakthru S 240 foram adicionados e os esporos foram bem dispersos. 250 L ou 0,25 g de cada amostra foram transferidos para um tubo Falcon de 50 mL estril. Os tubos foram preenchidos at 25 g usando uma soluo aquosa estril contendo 2% de Tween 80 e homogeinizados em vrtice para alcanar a primeira etapa de diluio (diluio de 1:100). Esta diluio foi usada para diluio adicional e manchamento em gar.[00139] Not all samples well mixed or fully mixed in 2% Tween 80. For these samples, an alternative method of dispersion / dilution was applied where the oil phase was removed from the spores first: 0.25 g or 250 L of The sample is weighed in a 2 ml Eppendorf tube, and 0.5 ml of 2% Tween 80 is added, and the mixture is transferred to an Eppendorf centrifuge where it is centrifuged for 1 minute at 10,000 rpm. The supernatant (= upper oily phase) is discarded using a pipette. Afterwards 250 L of Breakthru S 240 were added and the spores were well dispersed. 250 L or 0.25 g of each sample was transferred to a sterile 50 mL Falcon tube. The tubes were filled to 25 g using a sterile aqueous solution containing 2% Tween 80 and vortexed to achieve the first dilution step (1: 100 dilution). This dilution was used for further dilution and agar staining.

Espere at que o lquido seja absorvido pelo gar e transfira a placa de gar para uma incubadora e incube a 25C durante 17 horas. Abra a placa e coloque-a sob o microscpio. Se necessrio, conte mais de um campo por mancha.[00140] To evaluate the spore germination rate prepare a 1: 30000 dilution based on the 1: 100 dilution achieved by multiple automated dilution (pipetting robot, 96-well plate). Subsequently, 12 x 12 cm agar plates were taken and stained with 10 times 5 L of each sample using an automated 12-channel pipette. Wait until the liquid is absorbed by the agar and transfer the agar plate to an incubator and incubate at 25 C for 17 hours. Open the plate and place it under the microscope. Randomly choose an area per spot and record the number of germinated and non-germinated spores that are within the designated field. At least 200 spores per sample need to be evaluated. If necessary, count more than one field per spot.
